A leading governorship aspirant in Plateau State, Nde David Victor Dimka fsi, ex-Director of Nigeria Customs Service (NCS) has assured the people of Kanam LGA of the state that given his qualities and experiences in the service, he is better placed to secure Plateau State for meaningful development. Dimka stated this during his visit to the Local Government Area and was received by traditional rulers, the executive council represented by the deputy chairman, the legislative council and the APC Party Chairman and his Exco. In his remark at the event, the Wamban Kanam, Alhaji Hamza said the leader of the DVD has all the qualities of good leadership and is well exposed to guarantee peaceful coexistence and development in the State. Dimka thanked the entire people of Kanam for the warm reception and opening their doors to receive him and the Entourage. He described the people of Kanam as good neighbours who are historically united and straightforward. “As a fellow of the Security Institute, I must say that I am confident and have the qualities to secure Plateau State and develop it”. “Today I want to say without any fear of contradiction that I have seen hope in Kanam and I will not disappoint you if I become the governor in 2023”, he said. According to him, Plateau State needs a leader that can handle diversity. POLL While welcoming the DVD Leader, the Chairman of Kanam Local Government ably represented by his deputy Honourable Bala Haruna (aka P.A) said they were happy to have a digital Ngas man as a leader. “We are one and we must ensure that we support the movement towards making Plateau a secured and better State”.